verwrite files, when they were edited on a remote end but not yet fetch/synced locally)\n\nAdditionally we should require that a machine is `alwaysOn` before attempting to mount - or even better - ensure that klient's `usage` kite metchod, which is used by kloud to query the idle time, is taking mounts into account and does not allow for turning off a machine if it has active mounts. This is responsible for majority of \"broken\" mounts.\n\nSimilarly to https://github.com/koding/koding/issues/9252 we should allow for remote configuration of the machine - toggling `alwaysOn`, managing shared users etc.\n## Current Behavior\n\n`kd mount` sometimes fail.\n## Possible Solution\n\nIt should not.\n\n/cc @cihangir @devrim \n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/9306/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/9306/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/8965","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/8965/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/8965/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/8965/events","html_url":"https://github.com/koding/koding/issues/8965","id":175452241,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxNzU0NTIyNDE=","number":8965,"title":"klient/kd: configuration v2","user":{"login":"rjeczalik","id":1162017,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExNjIwMTc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1162017?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rjeczalik","html_url":"https://github.com/rjeczalik","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rjeczalik/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rjeczalik/following{/othe