:{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"If template's Resource map contains array values like `[]map[string]interface{}`, calling ShadowVariables will add values from template's ast.ObjectList tree to that resource. It should replace them instead.\n## Expected Behavior\n\nArray elements in final Resource object are not duplicated and contain valid shadowed variables.\n## Current Behavior\n\nArray elements in final Resource object are duplicated. \n## Possible Solution\n\n1 - Rewrite ShadowVariables function so it will not use hcl pacage - this one will need some work.\n2 - Hack hcl.DecodeObject function so it will merge all array elements instead of adding them. (probably bad idea but simpler that 1)\n3 - ??\n## Steps to Reproduce (for bugs)\n\nCode that demonstrates the problem: https://play.golang.org/p/wtTsxinMIP\n\nCode that causes the problem: https://github.com/koding/koding/blob/d767072a16ee25211bb6a2d20603a46060f96fb0/go/src/koding/kites/kloud/stack/provider/template.go#L217\n\nExact place where array variables are duplicated:\nhttps://github.com/hashicorp/hcl/blob/master/decoder.go#L456\n## Context\n\nAll users who specify array elements in their stack will end up with duplicated values. GCP instances require `disk` field to be of array type (because user can specify more than one). Because of this bug, specified disks are duplicated.\n\n/cc @cihangir @gokmen @rjeczalik \n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/9346/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":1,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/9346/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/9663","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/koding/koding/issues/9663/labe